         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [ ¶ The best thanks of the council ¶ were also ¶ A letter of condolence was also ordered to be sent to the widow of Judge Bindon. ¶ ordered ¶  ¶ to be forwarded to Baron Von Mueller, for ¶ his ¶ do...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.08.00g</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Bendigo School of Mines</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text used here is from a report of the 7 August 1879 meeting of the Council of the Bendigo School of Mines in 'School of Mines',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Bendigo advertiser</seg>, 8 August 1879, p. 2.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">The best thanks of the council<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">were also</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A letter of condolence was also ordered to be sent to the widow of Judge Bindon.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ordered</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">to be forwarded to Baron Von Mueller, for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">his<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">donation of an album containing 58 varieties of</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">pharmaceutical plants for the use of the school</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.]</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A similar set, of 60 specimens,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was also sent to the Ballarat School of Mines, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and announced at the meeting of the administrative council on 14 August 1879 ('Ballarat',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 16 August 1879, p. 5).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
